<TITLE> Hizb-ut-Tahrir member in remand </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 04 (bdnews24.com)  The Adabar police station has been allowed to take Hizb-ut-Tahrir member Nafis Salam Uday in remand for a day for questioning. Metropolitan magistrate Shamima Parvin has granted one day remand of Uday on Tuesday instead of the seven days the police had requested. He was arrested on Sunday night under Anti-terrorism Act from Mohammadia Housing area when he was distributing booklets of the organisation. On the other hand, Mohammadpur police has been granted another day of remand of Nur Mohammad, Mahmud Hasan, Maniruzzaman and Sakir Khan, members of the same organisation, after completion of their two days remand. The Chief Metropolitan Magistrates' Court granted the permission to question them in police custody on Tuesday. They were arrested on Friday from Mohammadpur area. 
